The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Team Bhupathi in quarters

New Delhi: Top seeds Mahesh Bhupathi and his Serb partner Nenad Zimonjic beat Spaniards Nicolas Almagro and Fernando Verdasco in straight sets to advance to the quarter finals of ATP Pilot Pen Classic tournament in New Haven, US. 

The Indo-Serb pair defeated their unseeded rivals 7-5, 6-3 in the first round of the $675,250 event on Monday. They will now be up against another unseeded Spanish pair of David Ferrer and Albert Montanes in the last-eight stage. 

Ferrer and Montanes beat the Argentine duo of Agustin Calleri and Juan Monaco 7-6 (3), 7-6 in their first-round match. (PTI) 




